Dependencies : llvm-3.2 clang 3.2 (optional) libkernelexpr

* llvm-3.2 *

The LLVM source code could be download from:
http://www.llvm.org/releases/3.2/llvm-3.2.src.tar.gz

It is also available directly from the LLVM svn server:
svn co http://llvm.org/svn/llvm-project/llvm/tags/RELEASE_32/final llvm

Or could be cloned from LLVM git repository:

git clone http://llvm.org/git/llvm.git llvm
cd llvm
git checkout --track -b release_32 remotes/origin/release_32

After building llvm-3.2, the path to LLVM_CONFIG needs to be updated in the Makefile.

* clang *
clang is needed to compile from OpenCL C (.cl) to spir (.bc)

see : https://github.com/KhronosGroup/SPIR

* libkernelexpr *

The variables KERNELEXPR_LIBDIR and KERNELEXPR_INCLUDEDIR must be set in the Makefile.

Compilation :
$ make

Usage :
You can use the script run.sh to test the pass, e.g:
$ ./run.sh spirfile.bc

example :
$ ./run.sh tests/kernels/for-0-64.ll
